AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: abstract
AnnotationProperty.skos:definition: An abstract class is a high level class or slot that is typically used to group common slots together and is generally not instantiated. When generating golr-views, abstract classes are ignored

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: alias
AnnotationProperty.skos:definition: A name to be assigned to the slot in implementations that is different that its type. The primary use for this is to allow class AND schema definitions to both have "slots" where one inline and the other a reference

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: classes
AnnotationProperty.skos:definition: classes defined in schema

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: default_curi_maps
AnnotationProperty.skos:definition: List of prefixcommon biocontexts to be fetched to resolve id_prefixes and inline prefix variables

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: default_prefix
AnnotationProperty.skos:definition: default and base prefix -- used for ':' identifiers, @base and @vocab

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: domain
AnnotationProperty.skos:definition: The class to which this slot applies.

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: generation_date
AnnotationProperty.skos:definition: date that the schema was loaded/generated. Supplied by the loader

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: id
AnnotationProperty.skos:definition: a globally unique id or url for a schema

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: id_prefixes
AnnotationProperty.skos:note: A list of CURI prefixes that are used in the representation of instances of the model. All prefixes in this list are added to the prefix sections of the target models. These prefixes are fetched from

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: inherited
AnnotationProperty.skos:definition: True means that the slot is an essential attribute of the container -- that the slot is carried across is_a and slot_usage paths

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: inlined
AnnotationProperty.skos:definition: if true then the value of this slot is inlined (i.e. a nested object) rather linked by key

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: license
AnnotationProperty.skos:definition: license for the schema

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: local_name
AnnotationProperty.skos:definition: the nsname (sans ':' for a given prefix)

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: mappings
AnnotationProperty.skos:definition: list of equivalent or skos exact mappings to an ontology class

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: metamodel_version
AnnotationProperty.skos:definition: Version of the metamodel used to load the schema. Supplied by the loader

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: multivalued
AnnotationProperty.skos:definition: If true slot can have many values

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: prefix_uri
AnnotationProperty.skos:definition: A URI associated with a given prefix

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: prefixes
AnnotationProperty.skos:definition: Additional prefixes to be added to the context beyond those fetched from prefixcommons in id_prefixes

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: primary_key
AnnotationProperty.skos:definition: True means that this serves as a unique identifier

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: range
AnnotationProperty.skos:definition: The slot type. Can be any class or type

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: slot_usage
AnnotationProperty.skos:definition: Additional info on how a slot is used in the context of a class. Many slots may be re-used across different classes, but the meaning of the slot may be refined by context. For example, a generic association model may use slots subject/predicate/object with generic semantics and minimal constraints. When this is subclasses, e.g. to disease-phenotype associations then slot_usage may specify both local naming (e.g. subject=disease) and local constraints

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: slots
AnnotationProperty.skos:definition: list of slot names that are applicable to a class. slots are by default inherited over is_a and mixins.

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: source_file
AnnotationProperty.skos:definition: name, uri or description of the source of the schema. Supplied by the loader

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: source_file_date
AnnotationProperty.skos:definition: modification date of the source of the schema. Supplied by the loader

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: source_file_size
AnnotationProperty.skos:definition: size in bytes of the source of the schema. Supplied by the loader

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: version
AnnotationProperty.skos:definition: Schema version

Class.rdfs:label: is_a
Class.skos:definition: specifies single-inheritance between classes and slots. While multiple inheritance is not allowed, mixins can be provided effectively providing the same thing. The semantics are the same when translated to formalisms that allow MI (e.g. RDFS/OWL). When translating to a SI framework (e.g. java classes, python classes) then is_a is used. When translating a framework without polymorphism (e.g. json-schema, solr document schema) then is_a and mixins are recursively unfolded

Class.rdfs:label: mixins
Class.skos:definition: List of definitions to be mixed in. Targets may be any definition of the same type

Class.rdfs:label: union_of
Class.skos:definition: list of class or slot definitions that are combined to create the union class

NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: class_definition_is_a
NamedIndividual.skos:definition: specifies single-inheritance between classes and slots. While multiple inheritance is not allowed, mixins can be provided effectively providing the same thing. The semantics are the same when translated to formalisms that allow MI (e.g. RDFS/OWL). When translating to a SI framework (e.g. java classes, python classes) then is_a is used. When translating a framework without polymorphism (e.g. json-schema, solr document schema) then is_a and mixins are recursively unfolded

NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: class_definition_mixins
NamedIndividual.skos:definition: List of definitions to be mixed in. Targets may be any definition of the same type

NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: class_definition_union_of
NamedIndividual.skos:definition: list of class or slot definitions that are combined to create the union class

NamedIndividual.skos:definition: specifies single-inheritance between classes and slots. While multiple inheritance is not allowed, mixins can be provided effectively providing the same thing. The semantics are the same when translated to formalisms that allow MI (e.g. RDFS/OWL). When translating to a SI framework (e.g. java classes, python classes) then is_a is used. When translating a framework without polymorphism (e.g. json-schema, solr document schema) then is_a and mixins are recursively unfolded

NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: slot_definition_mixins
NamedIndividual.skos:definition: List of definitions to be mixed in. Targets may be any definition of the same type

NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: slot_definition_union_of
NamedIndividual.skos:definition: list of class or slot definitions that are combined to create the union class

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Definition
rdf:Description.skos:definition: definition base class

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Example
rdf:Description.skos:definition: example of usage

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Prefix
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Prefix URI map

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: apply_to
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Used to extend an existing class definition. For example, if we have a core schema where a gene has two slots for identifier and symbol, and we have a specialized schema for my_organism where we wish to add a slot systematic_name, we can avoid subclassing by defining a class gene_my_organism, adding the slot to this class, and then adding an apply_to pointing to the gene class. The new slot will be 'injected into' the gene class.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: comment
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Comment about an element

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: default_type
rdf:Description.skos:definition: the default type if range is omitted

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: defining_slots
rdf:Description.skos:definition: The combination of is_a plus defining slots form a genus-differentia definition, or the set of necessary and sufficient conditions that can be transformed into an OWL equivalence axiom

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: description
rdf:Description.skos:definition: a description

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: examples
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Example of usage for a slot or class

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: flags
rdf:Description.skos:definition: State information and other details

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: from_schema
rdf:Description.skos:definition: id of the schema that the element was derived from. Supplied by the loader.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: identifier
rdf:Description.skos:definition: True means that this slot must be unique across the collection of slots

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: imports
rdf:Description.skos:definition: A list of modules that are imported into the schema

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: in_subset
rdf:Description.skos:definition: used to indicate membership of a term in a defined subset of biolink terms used for a particular domain or application (e.g. the translator_minimal subset holding the minimal set of predicates used in a translator knowledge graph)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: inverse
rdf:Description.skos:definition: used to indicate the inverse of a slot (e.g. 'expresses' is the inverse predicate of 'expressed in')

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: local_names
rdf:Description.skos:definition: map from local identifier to slot

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: mixin
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Used only as a mixin -- cannot be instantiated on its own.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: name
rdf:Description.skos:definition: a unique key that identifies a slot, type or class in a schema

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: note
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Notes about an element

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: object_property
rdf:Description.skos:definition: true means that this slot is part of the formal definition of a class

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: path
rdf:Description.skos:definition: For any denormalized slot, this represents the tree or graph path used to generate the denormalized form

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: required
rdf:Description.skos:definition: If true slot must have at least one value

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: singular_name
rdf:Description.skos:definition: a name that is used in the singular form

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: slot_definitions
rdf:Description.skos:definition: collection of slot definitions in a schema

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: subclass_of
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Ontolgy property which this is a subclass of. Not to be confused with is_a which links datamodel classes

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: subproperty_of
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Ontolgy property which this is a subproperty of

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: symmetric
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Symmetric slot
rdf:Description.skos:note: Indications that a slot or reified association is symmetric

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: typeof
rdf:Description.skos:definition: a builtin ('string', 'integer', 'float', 'double', 'boolean', 'time', 'uri') or another type definition

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: types
rdf:Description.skos:definition: types defined in schema

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: values_from
rdf:Description.skos:definition: identifies the possible uri's of the range

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: metamodel
rdf:Description.skos:definition: Metamodel for biolink schema
rdf:Description.skos:note: OIO prefix is not correct -- where IS "inSubset" derived from?
